betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§o"In The End, It Was a War Without Reason."§r
- IGoByLotsOfNames

Welcome to §4§lWARFACTORY§r!!!

This pack is intended to be played in a §bRealistic Terrain [RTG] Overworld dimension§r.

If you're playing with friends, don't forget to invite them to the §equestbook party§r.

§rIf you wish to build your base in a skyblock world, §4too bad!§r The void is not accessible here. Not yet. You need to stand and fight if you have any hope of survival.

That reminds me, you need to §cfight§r to survive. It's a hard world out there, but you have the technology to grab that world by the neck and wring it dry for all it's got!

Your first major crafting project!

The §6Steam Dynamo§r will be your source of §dpower§r for the early game. It requires §9Water§r and burnable fuel like §6Coal§r or §6Sugar Cane§r to produce power.

You'll need a small bit of §6Silver§r for this dynamo. If you haven't found a §6Galena vein§r yet (which is where Silver is), then consider "buying" some §6Silver Ore§r using §dNomicoins§r. You won't need a ton of silver and lead just yet, so it won't bankrupt you.

Keep in mind that §eDynamos only output power when burning through fuel, and only the block attached directly to the coil will get provided with power§r.

§6§lNote:§r §6In Warfactory, Steam Dynamo without any upgrades has maximum energy generation capacity of 20 RF/t, or §l5 EU/t. §r§6I recommend you slap a Boiler Conversion Augment into the dynamo. With the boiler conversion, the Steam Dynamo can produce up to §l80 steam/t§r§6, which can be converted into§l 40 EU/t§r§6 with GT Steam Turbines or Steam Dynamos with Turbine Augments. This also means that a Steam Dynamo with a Boiler Conversion augment will outperform any singleblock GT boilers.
A repeatable quest that gives you either a §6baguette§r (a nice treat), or a §cbehelit§r (a horrible demonic monster item that you can trade for §cburgers§r).

A little music shop for all your musical needs.

Includes all vanilla and modspecific discs, as well as §dNightcore§r and §cAmogus§r.

You are §cweak§r right now. You barely have the means to stand against the §5fragile ghouls in the dark§r.

But that will change.

In your hands is the heart of a new empire. This device - the §eCitadel Block§r - may be placed on the surface. Once done, the block will become a ward, and shall protect your land from those who would seek to take it from you. But be warned, §cit does not render you invulnerable§r.

An enemy with the §aright techniques§r and §asufficient firepower§r, can still conquer you.

Be quick. Be cautious. Be strong.

§o"Only the dead have seen the end of war,"§r they say. That seems like a load of rubbish to you. Your §amachines§r, coupled with your §5arcane knowledge§r, can put good use to all those useless skeletons sitting around.

You begin your research into necromancy. The flesh is weak. But the bones... Those are strong. 

Ever since you first woke up in orbit of this world, you've craved to create an army of the undead to do your bidding. Now, you can finally realize that dream.

The §7Baby Skeleton Maker§r is your first step. It lacks the channelling power to make adult-sized skeletons, so small ones will have to do. When fed bones and milk and attuned to your §bSeal§r, it can create baby skeletons to do your bidding.

Having an army of child soldiers is helpful, but not ideal. 

If you really want to keep your stuff safe, you need real soldiers. The time for a true §cArmy of the Dead§r is nigh.

The §4Skeleton Warrior Maker§r can create full-grown, bloodthirsty skeleton warriors en-masse. Just give it bones, milk, and an §bOverlord's Seal§r. 

If you're feeling adventurous, you can throw in a §6skinsuit§r and some §aadditives§r as well.

The §bOverlord's Seal§r uses a simple form of Sympathetic Magic to record your will and essence in a useable item. When placed in a Skeleton Maker, it will attune that skeleton to you. It will become your loyal follower, from death and beyond.
betterquesting:10.name:8: One Ring to Rule Them All

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The §7Squad Book§r is fairly simple once you get a hang of it. 

All you really need to do is §3write the names of different squads§r in each slot, and you'll be able to §aassign those squads§r to your skeleton warriors without any fuss.

By using your §bOverlord's Seal§r, you can give orders to all of your skeletons at once, or just to individual squads.

The §eCitadel§r is the heart of your new empire. Everything you own and everything you are is tied to this one block.

Once you have a citadel established, you can begin to place down §aClaim Blocks§r to conquer more chunks. Claim blocks are dirt cheap, so you shouldn't have to worry about running out anytime soon. Each claim block has a §bsiege resistance§r of 5.

§5Reinforced Claim Blocks§r are similar, but offer 10 §bsiege resistance§r instead, and are far more expensive.

There is only one valid way to conquer an enemy faction: through §6§lSIEGES§r.

The siege block, when placed adjacent to an enemy claim, is the launching point for your attack. A siege is, for the most part, a PVP fight between defenders and attackers. Certain actions will §cadd points§r to the attacker's side, and others will §9remove those points§r.

§e§lCitadels§r have §e§l15§r defense.

§d§lReinforced Claims§r have §d§l10§r defense.

§a§lBasic Claims§r have §a§l5§r defense.

Both sides can place §bflags§r (not actual items) at a besieged chunk to advance/recede the siege by 1 point.

Each of your side's deaths will add 1 point to the enemy side.

Every minecraft day, a siege increases by 1 point passively.

Skeletons are mostly made of §lCalcium§r. Thus, they need milk to heal and grow. 

§lMilk Bottles§r can be placed in a skeleton's inventory to §6level them up§r, or thrown at them to §cheal§r. They can be ccheaply bottled in a canning machine.

§lMilk Buckets§r can be fed directly to skeletons to rapidly heal them.
betterquesting:10.name:8: I Want to Get Off Mr. Bones' Wild Ride

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
With so many armies at your command, it would be foolish to call you anything other than a true §6§lKing§r. All these lands shall be yours. Your armies shall crush all who defy you, and your followers shall sing songs of your fair and noble leadership. A royal line of a thousand generations shall burst forth from your lifeblood. 

That is your fate. That is your birthright.

As you've progressed, you've found that your crude bolt action rifles won't do. You want, no, §oneed§r more firepower. With your new EBF simmering away in your base, you realize that you now have the alloys you need for the next step in gunsmithing.

That next step comes in the form of §3Medium-Voltage Guns§r. These weapons make full use of your new materials to operate in unprecedented ways. These new autoloading firearms will be able to fire far faster, in higher calibers and with fewer jams. 


You shudder to think of the §4§lfirepower§r that will soon be at your disposal.


Medium voltage guns can be found by searching §3$gunsMV§r.

Leave your old notions of warfare behind. This is a new age, and with it comes new means of conquest. Your dominion shall be forged §cnot at the edge of a blade§r, but §bat the tip of a missile§r.

With ICBMs, you need not look your enemy in the eye as you drain the life out of them. You may take lives without guilt, without any personal stakes. §6Murder has never been easier§r.

Your missiles can't just be launched from some patch of mud. They need a §2launchpad§r, and a system to guide them. This quest will force you to obtain everything you need to construct a fully-functional missile silo.

The §2Launcher Pad§r itself holds the missile in place.

The §2Launcher Screen§r ties into the missile's computer systems, allowing you to designate a target and launch when the time is right.

 §2Launcher Frames§r are not strictly necessary, but they do increase the missile's accuracy when placed next to it.

The  §2Launcher Connector§r allows you to tie your  §2Launcher Screen§r to  §2Launcher Pads§r not directly adjacent to it. You can daisy-chain multiple different pads together this way.

§cWarfactory§r wouldn't be §cWarfactory§r if it didn't have guns. Modern Warfare Cubed is fully implemented and gregified, with its best guns tied to an appropriate voltage tier.

In the beginning, you'll only have access to crude black powder weapons. Maybe a Mare's Leg if you're lucky. But as time goes by, you'll gain the ability to manufacture increasingly-powerful guns in §bAssembly Machines§r.

You will also gain access to body armor. You'll start with cheap police vests, and soon progress to advanced military gear and more!

This quest will see you crafting a §6Wrought Iron Gun Action§r. Actions and Receivers are the foundation for almost every gun you will make.
betterquesting:10.name:8: Guns and How to Use Them

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
In the modern age, no army is complete without its armor. §cWarfactory§r implements a dozen vehicles of war to choose from, from §btiny drones§r to §6massive tanks§r. Most of these vehicles are tiered at either MV or HV, so it may take some time to unlock them. It's well worth the wait, however.


You shouldn't need much guidance on how to use them. The interfaces and keybinds are relatively intuitive.

If you replace your §2Launcher Screen§r with a §2Radar Station§r, you can turn your missile system into an anti-missile system.

The Radar Screen will detect enemy missiles and release a launch authorization in response, automagically feeding the bogey's position to the missiles in its arsenal. Only §bSurface-To-Air§r missiles can successfully intercept an enemy ICBM.

Your targets won't always be continents away. Sometimes, you need to deliver huge amounts of hurt to someone right next door. That's what the §2Cruise Launcher§r is for.

In exchange for range, the §2Cruise Launcher§r integrates the screen and pad into a single block. This is useful as a close-in weapon system, a base defense tool, a raiding tool or as a means of masculine compensation.

The §4Laser Rangefinder§r does exactly what you'd expect it to: it stores coordinates for later use.

It's not much use normally, though. The coordinates it keeps are stored in the item until it is used on a launch screen, so you can't authorize a launch from in the field.
betterquesting:10.name:8: I Put A Spell On You

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The §2Laser Designator§r is the §4Laser Rangefinder§r with all the flaws removed. 

Not only can it store coordinates, but it can §6wirelessly stream those coordinates to a launcher§r and §bauthorize a launch§r, all in a single click!

It needs to be bounded to a launch screen, however. Make sure the frequency in the screen is something unique, or else others will be able to hack into your systems and launch your missiles for you.

You continue to push the cutting edge of your technology. Nothing is enough. Nothing will do. Your servants and researchers tire in their labs. They don't share your fear. They don't share your vision. 

You run a shaking hand through matted hair, so lost in thought that you can barely function. You have so many enemies. So many skulls you crave to put a bullet through. And §cnot enough guns.§r 

You find yourself at your firing range shortly after midnight. Your greatest scientists, too exhausted to stand up straight, present you with their latest creation: a gun receiver forged entirely from your newest, strongest alloys. Your scientists watch you with wide eyes, brimming with fear.

They speak of "deterrence", of "peace through firepower", but what do they know? Will their guns really put an end to war? No. Not when you've gotten so far. These guns will fuel that war. You can almost hear the screams, see §4blood§r gushing from fresh bullet holes in tattered enemy fatigues. Without realizing, you twist your face into a toothy grin and let out a breathless chuckle. 

Oh, yes. This will do well.


These guns can be found by searching §1$gunsIv§r.

Your new technologies are promising indeed. This §1Vanax Superclean Steel§r casts off the hard material limits of tungstensteel, boasting even stronger heat resistance and durability. With this new material, war has truly changed once and for all.

You instruct your soldiers to go forth, and claim what is rightfully yours! 

Your new machines shall §cstrike fears in the hearts of the wicked§r. You shall §4lay waste to all who defy you§r! You shall slaugher all, hear the sweet song of their death-screams and watch with glee as their houses burn and their spouses grieve! 

§cYour very name will embody fear and ruin for generations untold§r.


These guns can be found by searching §c$gunsLuv§r in JEI.

§8§o"Fate has set you free from human reason, and by providence, embrace your inner evil! Now stand, and face your future!"§r

You're finally ready to settle down. You have §eeverything you could ever want at your fingertips§r. A §6beautiful woman by your side§r. A §aprosperous empire under your banner§r. What more could you want?

According to the brainrot sigma edits you watch on Youtube, true sigmas §7"disregard women, acquire currency"§r. You already have enough money, so you decide to acquire something else instead: §cpower§r. Specifically killing power.

§6The Dead Sea scrolls§r speak of an ultimate weapon: a sword hewn from the stuff of the stars themselves. It is a blade which can strike down even gods. A blade truly limitless in its potential. The One who wields this Sword of the Desmos shall become unquestioned ruler of their realm. They shall be as a God. You §4crave§r this. That gnawing hunger for more occupies your every waking moment. It's just out of reach... Just a bit more work away.

To command such terrible power, you must pay a terrible price. Those ancient The hilt must be made from the bones of a living being, slaughtered as per the old rituals. No animal will do. Not even most humans. §cThe sacrifice must be someone close to the wielder§r, who loves them deeply and is, in turn, loved by them. 

This must be why you built the bonds you did. §9Your own wife is little more than a cog in the machine of your ascension.§r

§c§lYou've taken so many lives in your journey.§r §4§lWhat's one more?§r

ICBM has a few quirks. §bEMP§r devices are entirely broken and should not be used. §cBombs§r cannot be placed normally, but will work when placed in minecarts and detonated with activator rails.

Sorry about that.

The power of §l§3§lGreg§r is a pathway to many abilities some consider to be unnatural.

Starting at §d§lHV§r, you can use your microverse systems to send §cWizard Slayers§r to parallel dimensions. 

There, they shall experience a §6lifetime of glory§r. In exchange, they will give you the spoils of their quest. Their §3entire adventure§r shall span only a moment for you. 

They will provide you with §eShadow Wizard Money§r, which can be used in a laser engraver to create spellbooks.
The foundation for all magic. Can be obtained from §aflowers§r or infusing quartz blocks with §3primal mana§r.

A simple magical crafting table used for:


1. Upgrading §dWands§r

2. Binding Spells onto §bScrolls§r or §dWands§r.

3. Looking §6Cool§r.

The Imbuement Altar is good for two things:

1. Making cool clothes, and

2. Skipping carefully-curated progression that took hours and thousands of lines of CT scripts to make >:(

The second option is a total crapshoot, though. It takes ruined notebooks (which are insanely hard to obtain) and will only give you a random spell. So maybe it is balanced, after all.

As for your clothes, they really only serve aethestic purposes.


Why did I keep this thing in the game again?

This man is a §aWizard Hunter§r. He doesn't seem particularly strong, or smart, or capable, but he'll do. 

Once he's supplied with food and weaponry, you can use the §dMicroverse Projector§r to send him to another world. There, he will gradually gain the tools, companions and skills he needs to hunt down his targets. Your initial scans suggest that his target world is mild. It sits at a roughly-medieval level of technological progress, with a great abundance of whimsy and wonder. A good place to find wizards.

Of course, due to the relative fourth-dimensional quantum flux between parallal branes, years for him is but a moment for you. The whole process will finish in 30 seconds flat.

This is your second §eWizard Hunter§r. He stands at over seven feet tall, and has more muscles than what should be possible for a human being. He speaks in grunts and growls, managing only a few broken words of English in a booming voice.

He wears only crude furs and patches of pig-iron. You give him complete access to your formidable arsenal. He turns his nose up at all of your guns and alloy swords. Instead, he chooses a §6crude wooden axe§r as his weapon of choice. 

His §4target world§r is cold. Damp. Mountainous. The leylines seep with strange energies, affecting strange and disturbing changes on all those who dwell there. It is a land of chaos and debauchery, where blood-cults collect the very lives of their servants as tithes. The dark sorcerors who rule that land must be powerful indeed.

This §bwizard hunter§r is uniquely disquieting. He speaks in nonsensical rhymes and riddles. He often claims to see things that aren't there. Unfortunately, he performed perfectly in all of his training exercises, and there's nobody else more qualified than him.

You provide him with the strongest gear you can muster. He wears power armor, forged from ceramite and engraved in powerful wards, to deter even the fiercest demon. His sword is charged with the holy energy of the sun itself. But you doubt that it will be enough.

His target world is in shambles. Some sort of incursion - you struggle to find the words for it - broke down reality itself and let in a tide of demons. Your scans show mushrooms taller than trees that pulse with bioluminescent light. Carnivorous plants that can devour a man. Creatures of every imaginable shape and nature. And ruling it all; a race of sorcerors, half human and half something else, who have signed a pact with this perversion of nature to become something more. Something terrifying. 

Should you really open a door to this place?

A walking calamity. A hurricane in the shape of a man. All avert their eyes from this §l§4Wizard Slayer§r as he walks. He carries crude plate armor, and a sword longer than he is tall. You sense that he is human, but met with such a terrible fate that his mind has stretched beyond that.

He refuses to even look at your arsenal. Nothing you say seems to get through to him. He simply asks, in an eerily calm voice, where the §dMicroverse Projector§r is. 

The moment you open the Gate, a vast serpent rammed its head through. A thing larger than any skyscraper, with fiery eyes and thousands of rows of gnashing, yellow, needlelike teeth that clink against eachother like a vast windchime. Even the sight of it is almost too much to bear.

The world beyond is beyond description. It is a place of monsters: under a black sun and scarlet sky, seas of broiling primordial ooze play host to innumerable indescribable horrors, all locked in an endless war of teeth and claws and screams and roars. Beings of such immensity and power that a single one could lay waste to your entire planet. What sort of sorceror could survive, let alone rule, in such a place?

You urge the swordsman not to go. You worked so hard to find him - and it would be a tragedy to let him go to waste. He simply smiles and steps through.

The wizard hunter refuses to return. He has found a place to settle down there, and wishes to live the rest of his days among the spoils of his quest. You don't blame him. 

He sends you a small silk pouch as thanks. Inside is a small pile of §aShadow Wizard Money§r. Each note is a triangular section of treated papyrus, upon which innumerable magic glyphs are written. You can use your §bmachines§r to scan and process these symbols, to capture the magic within.

This §eWizard Hunter§r has done well for himself. With the dark sorcerors slain, he has taken their place as the ruler of that realm. He sits atop a throne of skulls, in the center of the grandest palace atop the highest mountain. Behind him is a great portrait of you as his patron being. He seems thankful.

He smiles - the first time you have seen him do so - and offers you a heavy fur sack. Inside are dozens of Wizard Coins.

These are different from the basic ones. They are made of solid gold instead of papyrus. Upon them are thousands of tiny gylphs, so small and so numerous that only an advanced machine could have etched them. They will do very nicely for your next set of spells.

The §bWizard Slayer§r appears at midnight. His armor is in shambles. His sword is reduced to barely a stump of metal above a sweatsoaked handle. He tosses you a severed head and you barely suppress the urge to jump back in fright. The head wears a crown of some unknown alloy. Half of its skin its human - the other half scaley and iridescent. Its eyes, slit like a snake's, are a brilliant violet. Its skull cavity is filled with §bShadow Wizard Coins§r.

The slayer begs you to free him from your service, and you have no choice but to honor his request. He leaves for the mountains to seek out some sort of solace in the twilight of his shortened life. 

The coins are forged from manasteel. The glyphs upon them are almost molecular in size, carved by some means which is far beyond you. You at least have the means to analyze them.

A flock of crows scatters into the air. The winds upon this moonless night blow sweet and steady.  At the far end of the field, just on the horizon, stands a §4familiar figure§r. You rouse from sleep and step outside your home. The grass is soft beneath your feet. 

The man that stands in front of you is almost unrecognizable.  His armor is nearly shattered. His sword is gone. A thousand new scars have joined the tapestry of his old ones. Where his eyes burned with hatred before, he now looks... content, almost.

He hands you a pile of §dShadow Wizard Coins§r. You struggle to tell if they are made of metal or flesh, as they somehow have the properties of both. They radiate a strange, alien aura - emotions and flashes of recollection grip your mind as you handle them. They seem to whisper their secrets into your mind.

The swordsman walks away without another word. Every muscle in his body seems to relax, as though some vast weight were taken off his shoulders.

You never see him again, but some part of you knows he's finally found the peace he sought.

Once you've obtained §6Shadow Wizard Coins§r, you need to copy the symbols within to use them. Thankfully, this is fairly simple.

A forming press can transcribe these glyphs onto a mundane book, thus turning it into a spellbook which can be used for casting.

From there, the information in a spellbook can be placed onto scroll via an §dArcane Workbench§r, which can in turn be bound to a §5Wand§r.

Wandcrafting can appear complex at first. Once you get into it, though, you'll find it's fairly intuitive.

You start with a §dNovice Wand§r. This can be crafted with a basic magic crystal for an all-arounder, or with an elemental crystal if you want to §6Specialize§r in any one type of magic.

They can be upgraded in an §dArcane Workbench§r via §5Tomes§r, which allows you to use higher-tier spells as you go.

Lastly, you can use the §dArcane Workbench§r to:

1. Add mana to wands by combining said wands with magic crystals,

2. Add spells to wands by combining wands with spellbooks.

§cWarfactory§r is a very complex modpack due to the high amount of §3§lGreg§r present. Having friends around will make it much easier.

Although this pack is geared towards §4WAR§r, you are far better off §acooperating§r with others. Make as many friends as you can, and grow your team as much as possible. Be willing to forge alliances too.

§lNever be afraid to extend the olive branch.

Guns are tiered into Gregtech's voltages. 

To start, you have a handful of §7ULV§r guns like the Mare's Leg or Contender. Those are simple enough to make entirely by hand.

Once you have an assembly machine, you can start manufacturing §7ULV§r-tier guns. These all require §3Wrought Iron Receivers§r and a handful of other earlygame components.

They can be found by searching §7gunsUlv§r.

While ULV-tier guns are decent for defending your property, they don't quite cut it for your use case. You need to put all hell of a lot of hurt downrange, fast. §cWrought iron won't cut it§r. You need to make §6Low-Voltage guns§r instead.

After tinkering around in your workshop, you've discovered how to make a §dSteel Gun Action§r using your more advanced construction techiques. It can withstand far higher temperatures and operate far longer without jamming.

As §6LV-tier§r guns are more complex than their predecessors, they require an §6assembly machine§r to make.

They can be found by searching §6$gunsLv§r.

No, this won't do at all! You need more firepower! You need to fire faster! Hurt things more!

You throw your blueprints to the floor in a fit of rage. There must be something stronger out there! Something better than steel!

Oh, but there is.

With §7Stainless Steel§r, you can craft a new receiver, to use for even more powerful guns. It takes the same action as a normal steel receiver, but uses a fully stainless-steel construction to enhance its tolerance for heat and prevent corrosion.

Finally, your dreams of destruction are within your grasp.

You can find these guns by searching §a$gunsHv§r.

§8§o"Holy Gregger, you've been down too long in the voltage sea. Oh, can't you see what I mean?"§r

You are married to your machines. §3Science§r is your bride. Your reason for being. You've been toiling away in the dark for so long that the §6glow of sunlight§r feels alien to you. You've forgotten the feeling of §2grass beneath your feet§r. If only, for a moment, you could rest. Perhaps after your next magnum opus.

You set your sights on finding companionship. Your first attempts do not go well. You mumble to women about "polycaprolactam", "the ancient Agarthan spirit", and "vanax superclean steel", unnerving most and chasing away the rest. For a time, it seems hopeless.

Eventually, you start putting yourself out there. Talking to people feels strange at first, especially for a recluse like yourself. But awkward small-talk turns into comfortable conversations, and you even make friends among the non-Gregic. In time, you §abegin to feel confident§r.

Of course, it takes time. It takes years to rebuild your social skills. But you forget about your timelines and start living in the moment, so it doesn't matter to you. You never believed someone like her could exist before she was staring you in the face. You can't exactly recall when you met her. A tennis club? A concert? Book club? Doesn't matter. But by then you knew just what to say. With the way her eyes lit up as you described the process of carboalkoxylation, you knew she was the one for you. 

From that point on, things went swimmingly. You're due to be married soon. Who thought that just §2touching grass§r could lead to this?

With your new advances in high-energy physics come new ways to take lives. Your research has brought you to the study of superalloys; the key to a whole new world of hurt. 

No longer are you bound by crude, unwieldy firearms. Your research has paved the way for ever-increasing rates of fire, bigger bullets and more death and destruction than you can imagine.

These guns can be found by searching §d$gunsEv§r.

There's a slot in the Skeleton Maker which is §labelled with a little PLUS§r. This is the §bAdditive Slot§r: certain items placed there will enhance your skeletons in certain ways.

- §7Iron Ingot§r: Resistance

- §5Obsidian§r: Resistance, Slowness, Fire Resistance

- §8Anvil§r: Fast Falling and Squashing Ability. Also resistance.

- §6Golden Apple§r: Regeneration

- §4Wither Skull§r: Wither on Attack (also Fire Resistance)

Sometimes, your skeletons can wander away. It happens to the best of us.

If you wanna §6drag them back§r, use a §6rallying horn§r. Also doubles as an easy way to annoy your teammates.

Your skeletons still have one major problem: §cthey're dead§r. Undead, more accurately. And you worry that commanding an army of walking dead might be bad for your PR.

You have breathed the §bforce of life§r into the dead, but have yet to make them §atruly alive§r. To do so, you build on some knowledge from Old Earth. §6The Ship's§r archives make note of the "Trainvoification" - an attempt to use a mix of technology and arcane knowledge to create sentient biological life from inanimate matter. 

You devise a means to recreate that with the technology at hand. Using simple biomass, a degradable rubber substrate and a human alchemical base, you can create a "Skinsuit": a mass of human stem cells programmed to clothe your skeletons in living flesh, effectively transforming them into living human beings.

Just place a skinsuit in a §cSkeleton Warrior Maker§r to apply it to the next skeleton.

Skinsuits can be §brenamed§r in an anvil to a player's username, whichs §bgives the skeleton that player's skin§r.

The alternative to §6Steam Dynamo + Turbine Conversion.§r

Just like the §6Steam Dynamo + Turbine Conversion§r, it consumes steam to produce power, at a ratio of §e2 Steam to 1 EU. §r
Technically,  §6Steam Dynamo + Turbine Conversion§r also consumes §62 Steam to produce 1 EU§r, but the dynamo only outputs §cRF§r, and you need a §cRF -> EU§r energy converter to transform §cRF§r into §cEU§r.

The §6LV Steam Turbine§r can produce up to 32 EU/t, which means it can consume up to 64 Steam/t.

If you check the recipe for the §6LV Steam Turbine§r, you might think that the sheer costs and crafting components might be way too expensive compare to the Steam Dynamo. However, §6Steam Dynamo§r often uses rare metals such as §bSilver§r or §eGold§r - ores that rarely spawns. §eGold Ores§r can only be found in magnetite veins, while §Ssilver Ore§rcan only be found in galena (a source of lead) veins. Meanwhile, §6LV Steam Turbine§r only consumes §7steel, copper, tin and rubber§r - resources which are plentiful in the overworld.
